: >
: >One should always assume that an attacker knows the system being used,
: >just not the key. 

: Aren't those requirement a little bit TOO harsh?  NO crypto system is
: safe against an attacker who knows the algorithm AND the key - right?

Just what I said. Assume the attacker knows the system and is trying
to find the key. Expecting to keep the system itself secret is
misguided.

